# A composable/conditional style={ … } interposed between TWO spreads (the ≥2
# fold trigger). Part B lowers the composable style as gsx.StyleString(…) into
# the folded bag's "style" entry, in source position between p and q, so the
# leaf's StyleMerged aggregates every style declaration in order and dedupes by
# CSS property (last occurrence wins): p's "margin:0" survives (distinct
# property); the composable "color:red" and q's "color:blue" collide on "color"
# and q (later in source order) wins.
